&lt;p&gt;TIKZ is a great language for producing vector graphics. It is however a bit tedious to go over the whole $\LaTeX$-like compilation when you get used to an ipython notebooks work-flow.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;I describe here how to use a &lt;em&gt;cell magic&lt;/em&gt; implemented  by  &lt;a href="http://www2.ipp.mpg.de/~mkraus/python/tikzmagic.py"&gt;http://www2.ipp.mpg.de/~mkraus/python/tikzmagic.py&lt;/a&gt; and  a hack to use euclide within the graph (as implemented in &lt;a href="https://github.com/laurentperrinet/ipython_magics"&gt;https://github.com/laurentperrinet/ipython_magics&lt;/a&gt;).&lt;/p&gt;
